docs.abstract: A school district confronts its segregated school system.
docs.snippet: A school district confronts its segregated school system.
docs.lead_paragraph: MAPLEWOOD, N.J — This suburb, with its high-performing schools, seems a haven of diversity and progressiveness. Signs that trumpet “Stigma-free Town” and “Hate Has No Home Here” hang from lampposts and, after a series of fatal police shootings across the country, “Black Lives Matter” placards popped up on lawns.

headline.main: A Suburb Believed in Liberal Ideals. Then Came a New Busing Plan.

docs.abstract: Five years after Eric Garner’s death, it’s painfully obvious that the daily anxiety black and brown people experience is justified.
docs.snippet: Five years after Eric Garner’s death, it’s painfully obvious that the daily anxiety black and brown people experience is justified.
docs.lead_paragraph: Last week, while the officer who had held Eric Garner in a banned chokehold as he said “I can’t breathe” about a dozen times was still employed by the New York Police Department, I was thousands of miles away, in Arizona, where I found myself terrified by a different set of law enforcement officials.

headline.main: Daniel Pantaleo Was Fired. We’re Still Afraid for Our Lives.

docs.snippet: For many members of the force, the decision to fire the officer whose chokehold led to Eric Garner’s death signaled a shift in the rules of engagement.
docs.lead_paragraph: The video of the final moments in the life of Eric Garner and his cries for help — “I can’t breathe” — ignited swift outrage, launching a campaign against aggressive policing and fueling the Black Lives Matter movement.
